narrativeSections.content:
WHEREAS the Client is a company duly registered and incorporated in terms of the Companies Act 71 of 2008 and carries on business as a management consulting firm;

AND WHEREAS the Client requires legal services in connection with commercial contract review and advisory;

AND WHEREAS the Firm has the requisite expertise and capacity to provide such services;

The Firm shall provide the following legal services to the Client:
1. Review and advice on commercial agreements;
2. Drafting and negotiation of service level agreements;
3. General commercial legal advisory as requested from time to time.
